        2. As a user, I should be able to assign
        tasks by clicking on Task tab under Active Stream.

        1. User should be able to click on ""High Priority"" checkbox to set the current task to a top priority task.
        Test steps:
            1) Login as HelpDesk - Expected result: Successful login
            2) Select "Task" tab on Activity Stream grid - Expected result: Empty create "Task" form
            3) Enter Task title, enter Task description, Select "High Priority" checkbox, press Send button - Expected result: View Task alert
            4) Enter into Created Task window - Expected result: Title and Description of the Task match with entered test data
            5) Verify that "High Priority" element is enabled - Expected result: "High Priority" element position "0 -122px"

        2. User should be able to click on Visual Editor and see the editor text-bar displays on top of the message box.
        Test steps:
            1) Login as HelpDesk - Expected result: Successful login
            2) Select "Task" tab on Activity Stream grid - Expected result: Empty create "Task" form
            3) Press on "A" button, which shows the "Visual Editor" panel - Expected result: The element is clickable
            4) Verify that "Visual Editor" is visible - Expected result: "Visual Editor" panel has more that 0 elements

        3. User should be able to click on upload files icon to upload files and pictures from local disks, download from external drive,
            select documents from bixtrix24, and create files to upload.
            1) Login as HelpDesk - Expected result: Successful login
            2) Select "Task" tab on Activity Stream grid - Expected result: Empty create "Task" form
            3) Enter Task title, enter Task description, press "Upload Files" button on buttons bottom panel
            4) Press upload files and images link - Expected result: Link is clickable
            5) Select file location from local disk and press Sent button - Expected result: View created Task Alert
            6) Verify that file is attached to created Task - Expected result: attached file name matches to test data

        4. User should be able to create a quote by clicking on the Comma icon.
         Test steps:
             1) Login as HelpDesk - Expected result: Successful login
             2) Select "Task" tab on Activity Stream grid - Expected result: Empty create "Task" form
             3) Enter Task title - Expected result: Title shows entered data
             4) Press on " button located on buttons bottom tab - Expected result: yellow background in Task description area
             5) Enter text to Task description - Expected result: Text is visible in Task description area
             6) Enter into Created Task window - Expected result: Title and Description of the Task match with entered test data

        5. User should be able to add mention by clicking on the Add mention icon and select contacts from the lists provided in dropdown.
        6. User should be able to attach link by clicking on the link icon.
        7. User should be able to click on ""Checklist"" to create checklists items(Things to do). User can add a checklist
           item by clicking on add button or check mark. User can add separator lines between checklist items. User can delete a checklist item by clicking on x mark.
        8. User can assign the tasks to employees by clicking on Add More and selecting contact from E-mail user, Employees
           and Departments and Recent contact lists. Employees can be added in different assignment categories: Created By, Participants and Observer.
        9. User can add Deadline, Time Planningby using date pickers.
        10. User can click on More to specify the task details.


